9.19.24  12:09 pm   at ~2:34-2:37 of Tommy Flanagan's Confirmation from the Eclypso album. I understand this part in the composition is a ii V I into G7. But is his left hand on the offbeats playing G half diminished, G minor add 2, Esus4? Which, adding in the bass, would be G half diminished over a, G minor add 2 over D, Esus4 over G -- does that sound like what he's playing to you?

      in the left hand, i'm hearing first [G C# F] then [Bb C F (plus possible F# with the left pinky)] then [F A B E]. intuitively this feels like the chord symbols would be Aaug7, Daug7#9, G13(9). plot twist though, bass actually hits C on that first chord and does it that way every time probably. bass is more thinking of it like C6, D7, G7
